                                '<em>forþfaran - to die</em>', only the
                                second part of the verb conjugates and it conjugates as it would normally. For example, 
                                the past second person singular of '<em>ofersteppan</em>' is '<em>þu
                                oferstope</em>', following the conjugation of '<em>steppan</em>'.
                            </p>
                        </div>
